ed through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","The case study connects implementation decisions to relevant roadmap skills and explains why alternatives were not chosen.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness.","The project is packaged so a reviewer can understand the artifact without live mentoring."]'::jsonb),
('proj-open-source-cloud-contribution', 'ph-cloud-capstone', 102, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Cloud Open Source Contribution', 'Optional practice project: Build and document Optional Cloud Open Source Contribution as a practical Cloud Engineer deliverable.', 'side', 5, 'advanced', '{"project":true,"projectBrief":"Build and document Optional Cloud Open Source Contribution as a practical Cloud Engineer deliverable.","projectKind":"cloud_infrastructure","projectScope":"small_practice_artifact","projectPurpose":"Practice the surrounding roadmap segment through a small reviewable artifact.","phaseContext":"Production Cloud Engineering Capstone","deliverable":"a reviewable Cloud Open Source Contribution configuration, deployment, or architecture lab with setup notes","skillsToPractice":["Cloud Architecture"],"suggestedSteps":["Define the Cloud Open Source Contribution scenario, target user or reviewer, and the specific Production Cloud Engineering Capstone concepts it will demonstrate.","Draw the target architecture, trust boundaries, environment variables, and deployment assumptions.","Create the smallest reproducible configuration or deployment that demonstrates the infrastructure concept.","Add identity, networking, health, cost, or rollback notes where relevant to the project brief.","Capture deployment output, configuration snippets, diagrams, or screenshots that a reviewer can inspect.","Document how to run or review the Cloud Open Source Contribution deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"expectedEvidence":["a reviewable Cloud Open Source Contribution configuration, deployment, or architecture lab with setup notes.","README or notes that explain setup, usage, assumptions, and expected output.","Architecture diagram or configuration snippets, deployment output, and rollback or teardown notes.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":true,"milestone":false,"source":"platform-generated","nodeKey":"proj-open-source-cloud-contribution"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Cloud Architecture through a focused Cloud Open Source Contribution artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a reviewable Cloud Open Source Contribution configuration, deployment, or architecture lab with setup notes is available for review.","The Cloud Open Source Contribution scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb);
